comments.body:
And Max, just want to doublecheck--there is no need to worry about other punctuations, right? We have all sorts of them: 

- apostrophe (')
- hyphen (-)
- ampersand (&), as in "Sac & Fox Nation, Oklahoma" (e.g. 9983461073506421)
- and even question mark, pound sign as in [Salt River First Nation [pound sign]195](https://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no2015119976.html), slash as in "Kuujjuarapik/Whapmagoostui (Inuit/Cree community)," but we don't have any bibs with those subject headings at this point.

For example, will the record 9922500203506421 (_A few acres of snow : the saga of the French and Indian Wars_) be tagged? It contains the string "United States--History--King George's War, 1744-1748."
